column5: Anyone see this hog yet?  http://rjnbirdeesoutdooradventures.blogspot.com/2010/12/dale-mcnair-lands-another-giant.html  Congrats Dale...nice beast
Thanks for posting that Matt, it's a great story and another awesome fish in the boat for Dale.
Three hundred hours, two fish.  That is dedication. What a beauty of a fish.
Dang that was a great read and congrats again to you Dale that is yet another fish of a life time it goes to show that you have to put in the time to get the big girls.  Cheers Mike
Another fat beast   ....congrats again Dale!...you and Sal are Hard Core for sure!
wow, what an awesome fish. my adrenaline would still be pumping from that.

Wow, another giant is right! Congrats to Dale on another monster. That is dedication without a doubt. He deserves it putting that much time in! I guess he'll be satisfied for another couple of years now lol.
That's an amazing muskie! Confidence, dedication, and time on the water is what catches fish. Congrats on another true trophy.
Oh my goodness, that is one fat muskie.....Wow!!!! Congratz to Dale   :clapping:
Great story, thanks for posting.  What a beauty!!!  Joey

Thanks for posting that link Matt.  I never want to be seen as a "spammer" to this community, though this is just a great story I felt lucky enough to get last night.  Dale is a down to earth guy that is just as hardcore as they come with regards to Muskies.  Hats off to him.  RJ
That's an inspiring fishing story.  Awesome fish!
Looks like that fish swallowed a keg  Superior catch, won't be surprise if we see another monster live release again....
Must have been cold, look at the ice on the rod, and the tail of the fish. Congrats to Dale for his dedication!
What a great read....thanks for posting that!
Congrats to Dale and Sal. They definately put the time in on the water!
